# BROWSER-notifications.md - Medium Notification & Reply Detection Patterns

## § 1. Extract Notifications

Page: `https://medium.com/me/notifications` (embed 3s wait in evaluate)

Only returns actionable types (response + note). Follows/subscribes/claps filtered out in JS.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const tabpanel = document.querySelector('div[role=\"tabpanel\"]'); if (!tabpanel) return { count: 0, items: [] }; const notifications = Array.from(tabpanel.children); const items = []; for (let i = 0; i < notifications.length && items.length < 10; i++) { const n = notifications[i]; const text = n.innerText; const isResponse = text.includes('responded'); const isNote = text.includes('left a note'); if (!isResponse && !isNote) continue; const author = text.split(String.fromCharCode(10))[0] || ''; if (author.toLowerCase().includes('{{handle_slug}}')) continue; const links = Array.from(n.querySelectorAll('a')); const aLink = links.find(a => a.href.includes('/p/')); items.push({ type: isResponse ? 'response' : 'note', author: author.slice(0, 40), articleUrl: aLink ? aLink.href.split('?')[0] : '' }); } return { count: items.length, items }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

